def convert_input_framed(Xmag):
  i = 0
  XmagT =Xmag.T
  XmagT_aug = np.concatenate((XmagT,np.ones(shape=(19,XmagT.shape[1]))*0.1), axis=0)
  print('X.shape = ',XmagT_aug.shape)
  Xmag_framed = []
  while i+20<=XmagT_aug.shape[0]:
    Xmag_framed.append(XmagT_aug[i:i+20,:].reshape(20,XmagT.shape[1],1))
    i+=1

  Xmag_framed=np.array(Xmag_framed)
  return Xmag_framed

Constructing the 2D CNN model¶

In [264]:
model_2d = Sequential([

    # Conv1D(64, 3, activation='relu', strides=2),
    # MaxPooling1D(),
    # Dropout(0.5),
    Conv2D(128, kernel_size=(16,10), activation='relu', input_shape=(20,513, 1), strides=2 , kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeUniform()),
    # MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2),

    Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(20,513, 1), strides=2 , kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeUniform()),
    # MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=2),

    Conv1D(12, kernel_size=5, activation='relu', strides=2, kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeUniform()),
    # MaxPooling1D(),

    Flatten(),
    # Dense(1024, activation='relu'),
    # Dropout(0.2),

    Dense(513, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeUniform())
    
]
)

model_2d.compile(
    # loss = 'msle',
    loss = 'mse',
    optimizer = Adam(learning_rate=0.001),
    metrics = ['Accuracy']
)

model_2d.summary()

from plotly.subplots import make_subplots
import plotly.graph_objects as go

fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=("Training Loss", "Training Accuracy"))

fig.add_trace(
    
    go.Scatter(y=model_2d_fit.history['loss'],
               line_color='red',
               name='Training Loss'
               ),
    row=1, col=1
)

fig.add_trace(
    
    go.Scatter(y=model_2d_fit.history['Accuracy'],
               line_color='blue',
               name='Training Accuracy'
               ),
    row=1, col=2
)
fig.update_yaxes(title_text="loss", row=1, col=1)
fig.update_yaxes(title_text="accuracy", row=1, col=2)
fig.update_layout(height=600, width=800, title_text="HW2:P3 ConvD model metrics")
fig.show()
